SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for UV protection, the range is 1.0V~3.54V, 20.0mV/step, the base is 1.0V.

SFL.Description: 1:send BATUVPF after UV shutdown confirmed,but before shutdown,0:no BATUVPF function.

SFL.Description: Threshold for discharge current,the range is 0.25mV~2.125mV on the sense resistor,0.125mV/step,the base is 0.25mV

SFL.Description: Threshold for charge current,the range is 0.125mV~1.0625mV on the sense resistor, 0.0625mV/step,the base is 0.125mV.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: Zero disables the DFET PF function. DFET PF will be generated if discharge current is more than this threshold for defined delay time while the discharge FET is OFF

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: When DEFT PF occurred, 1: blow fuse, 0: don’t blow fuse.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: Zero disables the CFET PF function.CFET PF will be generated if discharge current is more than this threshold for defined delay time while the discharge FET is OFF

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: When CEFT PF occurred, 1: blow fuse, 0: don’t blow fuse.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: COCP release method.0:timer release with 32s fixed,1:charger-off release.

SFL.Description: Charge Over Current Level2 (COC2) threshold(directly goes to analog).

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: Discharge Over Current Level2 (DOC2) threshold(directly goes to analog).

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: DOT threshold with 120uA reference current.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: DOT release hysteresis with 1.25mV/step,so the actual DOT release threshold:actual_dotr_th[12:0] = {2’b00, dot_th[8:0], 2’b00} + {4’b0000, dotr_hys[6:0], 2’b00}.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: COT release hysteresis with 2.5mV/step,so the actual COT release threshold:actual_cotr_th[12:0] = {1’b0, cot_th[8:0], 3’b000} + {3’b000, cotr_hys[6:0], 3’b000}.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: COT threshold with 120uA reference current.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: DUT threshold with 12uA reference current ( 16LSB/step =16x0.3125mV/step=5mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: DUT release hysteresis with 5mV/step,so the actual DUT release threshold:actual_dutr_th[12:0] = {cot_th[8:0], 4’b0000} - {2’b00, cotr_hys[6:0], 4’b0000}.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: CUT release hysteresis with 2.5mV/step,so the actual CUT release threshold:actual_cutr_th[12:0] = {1’b0, cut_th[8:0], 3’b000} - {3’b000, cutr_hys[6:0],3’b000}.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: CUT threshold with 12uA reference current 2.5mV/step.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT threshold with 120uA reference current ( 2LSB/step =2x0.3125mV/step=0.625mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT release hysteresis with 0.625mV/step,so the actual FETOT release threshold:actual_fetotr_th[12:0] = {3’b000, fetot_th[8:0], 1’b0} + {5’b00000, fetotr_hys[6:0], 1’b0}

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: CELLOT_PF threshold with 120uA reference current ( 4LSB/step =4x0.3125mV/step=1.25mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT_PF threshold with 120uA reference current (2LSB=2x0.3125mV/step=0.625mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Description: the cell voltage to start Cell Balance (CB), the range is 3.0V~4.26V, 20mV/step, the base is 3.0V.

ItemList.Item: Do balance in idle-state or in charge-state;
Do balance just only in idle-state.
Do balance just only in charge-state.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: when cell unbalance has been more than this threshold for defined delay time under check conditions, UB event will be generated to turn off both CFET and DFET, meanwhile send interrupt to MCU.

ItemList.Item: detect UB only in charge state
detect UB in charge state and in idle state

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: '0': detect UB only in charge state,'1': detect UB in charge state and in idle state.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: '0': no UB PF,'1':enable UB PF (this means that UB_PF will be generated once UB has been detected and confirmed).

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: the unbalance will not be checked until the maximum cell voltage is higher than this threshold, the actual threshold actual_ub_chk_th[12:0] = {1’b1, ub_chk_th[7:0], 4’b0000} with LSB = 0.625mV, so the range is 2.56V~5.11V, 10.0mV/step.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: ‘0000’: output active high; others: PWM output with duty 2x(N+1),where N = 1 ~ 15 corresponds to ‘0001’~‘1111’,so it covers 4~32 cycles of 32kHz,the PWM frequency is fixed at 1Hz.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: if the byte is 0x76, that means the user configuration has been programmed, and ready for mapping, meanwhile chip erase and byte erase/programming are prohibited for data protection except for this byte itself, which can be always allowed for byte erase when some conditions met, so that it can give chance to re-program the YFLASH after YFLASH is frozen by 0x76. Other value means this YFLASH is fresh and can be erased with chip erase or byte erase, and can be programmed.

SFL.Name: YFLASHConfig
SFL.Description: 8bits CRC (X^8 + X^2 + X + 1) check is used for USER data (0x0~0xE).

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: COV protection threshold for each cell.

ItemList.Item: select OVP range 4.0V~4.5V for Li_ion Cobalt//Monganate type
select OVP range 3.5V~4.0V for Li_ion Phosphate type

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: select COV range 4.0V~4.5V for Li_ion Cobalt type,'1':select COV range 3.5V~4.0V for Li_ion Phosphate type.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Hysteresis for COV release(comparator-based);the range is 50mV ~ 400mV with 50mV/step..

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: CUV protection threshold for each cell (comparator-based).

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: '0':CUVR voltage release,'1':CUVR voltage and load-open release.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Hysteresis for CUV release (comparator-based);the range is 100mV ~ 800mV with 100mV/step.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Cell under-voltage delay time (comparator-based), for covuv_scan = 62.5ms, the delay time is (N+1)x0.125s (0.125s ~ 4s), 0.125s/step; and for covuv_scan = 250ms, the delay time is (N+1)x0.25s (0.25s ~ 8s), 0.25s/step.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: ADC-based threshold for OV level1 protection.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Sigma-Delta ADC offset calibration for the system/board level, the range is +/-1mV with step = 1LSB = 7.8125uV. this offset will be subtracted from CADC data automatically in hardware internally for coulomb counting.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for UV protection, the range is 1.0V~3.54V, 20.0mV/step, the base is 1.0V.

ItemList.Item: select 3.3V as default LDO3.3V output for MCU

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: "0" to select 3.3V as default LDO3.3V output for MCU,"1" to select LDO5.0V output for MCU.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: hysteresis voltage for UV release, the range is 20mV~1.26V.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: BATUV shutdown threshold =(uvp_th[6:0] – batuv_shutdown_delta[5:0]) X cell_num.

ItemList.Item: send BATUVPF after UV shutdown confirmed,but before shutdown

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: 1:send BATUVPF after UV shutdown confirmed,but before shutdown,0:no BATUVPF function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for discharge current,the range is 0.25mV~2.125mV on the sense resistor,0.125mV/step,the base is 0.25mV

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for charge current,the range is 0.125mV~1.0625mV on the sense resistor, 0.0625mV/step,the base is 0.125mV.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for DOC1 protection,the range is 1.0mV~255mV,1.0mV/step.Zero will disable this function

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: DOC/1/DOC2/SC release method.0:timer release with 32s fixed,1:load-off release.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Zero disables the DFET PF function. DFET PF will be generated if discharge current is more than this threshold for defined delay time while the discharge FET is OFF

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: When DEFT PF occurred, 1: blow fuse, 0: don’t blow fuse.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Zero disables the CFET PF function.CFET PF will be generated if discharge current is more than this threshold for defined delay time while the discharge FET is OFF

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: When CEFT PF occurred, 1: blow fuse, 0: don’t blow fuse.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Threshold for COC1 protection,the range is 1.0mV~255mV,1.0mV/step.Zero will disable this function

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: COCP release method.0:timer release with 32s fixed,1:charger-off release.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Charge Over Current Level2 (COC2) threshold(directly goes to analog).

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: Discharge Over Current Level2 (DOC2) threshold(directly goes to analog).

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: DOT threshold with 120uA reference current.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: DOT release hysteresis with 1.25mV/step,so the actual DOT release threshold:actual_dotr_th[12:0] = {2’b00, dot_th[8:0], 2’b00} + {4’b0000, dotr_hys[6:0], 2’b00}.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: COT release hysteresis with 2.5mV/step,so the actual COT release threshold:actual_cotr_th[12:0] = {1’b0, cot_th[8:0], 3’b000} + {3’b000, cotr_hys[6:0], 3’b000}.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: COT threshold with 120uA reference current.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: DUT threshold with 12uA reference current ( 16LSB/step =16x0.3125mV/step=5mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: DUT release hysteresis with 5mV/step,so the actual DUT release threshold:actual_dutr_th[12:0] = {cot_th[8:0], 4’b0000} - {2’b00, cotr_hys[6:0], 4’b0000}.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: CUT release hysteresis with 2.5mV/step,so the actual CUT release threshold:actual_cutr_th[12:0] = {1’b0, cut_th[8:0], 3’b000} - {3’b000, cutr_hys[6:0],3’b000}.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: CUT threshold with 12uA reference current 2.5mV/step.Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT threshold with 120uA reference current ( 2LSB/step =2x0.3125mV/step=0.625mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT release hysteresis with 0.625mV/step,so the actual FETOT release threshold:actual_fetotr_th[12:0] = {3’b000, fetot_th[8:0], 1’b0} + {5’b00000, fetotr_hys[6:0], 1’b0}

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: CELLOT_PF threshold with 120uA reference current ( 4LSB/step =4x0.3125mV/step=1.25mV/step). Zero will disable this function.

SFL.Name: RegisterConfig
SFL.Description: FETOT_PF threshold with 120uA reference current (2LSB=2x0.3125mV/step=0.625mV/step). Zero will disable this function.
